sentences: Marta Canales Pizarro (17 July 1893 – 6 December 1986) was a Chilean violinist, choral conductor and composer.
She was born in Santiago and made her debut as a violinist at age eleven playing Mendelssohn's "Concerto".
With her brothers, she founded a chamber ensemble that was active from 1916–1920.
"Madrigales Teresianos", collection of twelve chorals, four mixed voices on the poetry of St. Teresa of Jesus (1933)
